      <section eId="sec_CC-3520">
        <num>CC 3520</num>
        <heading>Section </heading>
        <subsection eId="CC-3520__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>A marriage that is valid in the state where contracted, or in the state
where the parties were first domiciled as husband and wife, shall be treated as
a valid marriage unless to do so would violate a strong public policy of the
state whose law is applicable to the particular issue under Article 3519.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CC-3520__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>A purported marriage between persons of the same sex violates a
strong public policy of the state of Louisiana and such a marriage contracted
in another state shall not be recognized in this state for any purpose, including
the assertion of any right or claim as a result of the purported marriage.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=110540</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
